Overview
TheMulti-User MEMSProcesses, or MUMPsTM, is a well-
established commercial program that provides customers with cost-
effective access to surface micromachining for prototyping activities
and a seamless transition into manufacturing.
Aprogramoffered exclusively byCronos (acquired by MEMScAP,
Nov.1,2002),is designedfor general purpose micromachiningby
various users who wish to design and fabricate MEMS devices.
MUMPsTM was established in Dec.1992and has81runs in Oct.
2008.Cronos has renamedMUMPs as PolyMUMPs in2002in
order to announce their new SOIMUMPs (9th run, 2003) and
MetalMUMPs.
